<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-07T20:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-07T20:36:00-05:00" n="983" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d983">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/3401</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_HEJ1" type="from">(<hi rend="italic">Hale</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-07T20:00:00-05:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1916, 8 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 8, 7.30 p.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Costa Rican Minister for Foreign Affairs has called to ask advice as
                            follows:</p>
                        <p>He says that the Italian Minister two weeks ago telegraphed to know if
                            the Costa Rican Government would admit into its ports an Italian
                                [merchant<note n="2" xml:id="d983fn2">Word inserted according to a
                                further explanatory telegram of February 8.</note>] vessel “armed
                            against submarines.” He replied, “No.” He received to-day another
                            telegram from the Italian Minister saying that the United States had
                            granted a similar request. He says that the Costa Rican Government
                            desires to conform to the policy of the United States and that he asks
                            advice in the present case. Please instruct me by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HEJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hale</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>